A World Food Programme official said that food supply chains in Ukraine were collapsing, with key infrastructure such as bridges and trains destroyed by bombs and many grocery stores and warehouses empty. Hundreds of cows risk being slaughtered in Italy due to the conflict in Ukraine, which is a major global supplier of animal feed — stocks of which are falling fast across import-reliant southern Europe. Ivan Fedorov, the mayor of the occupied Ukrainian city of Melitopol, tells CNN’s Anderson Cooper what happened when he was kidnapped by Russian troops and held for six days.